HEADWORD: Hexane
<hw>Hex"ane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"e`x</grk>
six.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of five hydrocarbons,
<chform>C6H14</chform>, of the paraffin series. They are colorless,
volatile liquids, and are so called because the molecule has
<xex>six</xex> carbon atoms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

